<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1039,1318]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1039,1065]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body pale white with violet pigments on Ant III–IV, Ant II and femur I–III distally; Th II projected anteriorly and with 14 anterior, 7 median (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[638,699,1075,1101]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">m1ip</emphasis>
absent, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,832,1075,1101]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">m4</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[890,934,1075,1101]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">m4i</emphasis>
present) and 11 posterior mac (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1300,1330,1075,1101]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">p3</emphasis>
present); Th III–Abd II with 9, 5, 4 central mac respectively (
<figureCitation box="[737,841,1111,1138]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[249,1339,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12A–E. Lepidocyrtinus ryozoi nom. nov. (modified from Yosii 1959); A, chaetotaxy of Th II to Abd II (left side); B, chaetotaxy of Abd IV (left side); C, distal tibiotarsus and empodial complex III; D, chaetotaxy of the manubrial plate and proximal dens (dorso-lateral view); E, distal dens and mucro (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4392541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4392541/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
); Abd IV with 17 central mac and 8 lateral mac (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[249,1339,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12A–E. Lepidocyrtinus ryozoi nom. nov. (modified from Yosii 1959); A, chaetotaxy of Th II to Abd II (left side); B, chaetotaxy of Abd IV (left side); C, distal tibiotarsus and empodial complex III; D, chaetotaxy of the manubrial plate and proximal dens (dorso-lateral view); E, distal dens and mucro (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4392541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4392541/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
); unguis a.t. present; unguiculus with all lamella acuminate and toothless (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1157,1147,1174]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[249,1339,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12A–E. Lepidocyrtinus ryozoi nom. nov. (modified from Yosii 1959); A, chaetotaxy of Th II to Abd II (left side); B, chaetotaxy of Abd IV (left side); C, distal tibiotarsus and empodial complex III; D, chaetotaxy of the manubrial plate and proximal dens (dorso-lateral view); E, distal dens and mucro (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4392541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4392541/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
); manubrial plate with 3 blunt mac; dens with 9–10 blunt mac apically nipple-like (
<figureCitation box="[806,910,1183,1210]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[249,1339,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[249,1339,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12A–E. Lepidocyrtinus ryozoi nom. nov. (modified from Yosii 1959); A, chaetotaxy of Th II to Abd II (left side); B, chaetotaxy of Abd IV (left side); C, distal tibiotarsus and empodial complex III; D, chaetotaxy of the manubrial plate and proximal dens (dorso-lateral view); E, distal dens and mucro (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4392541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4392541/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
